The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 31: With expenditure far exceeding receipts, the Centre?s fiscal deficit during the first quarter crossed 50 per cent of the budget estimates of Rs 1,48,686 crore for the entire 2006-07. At Rs 77,740 crore, the fiscal deficit has accounted for 52.30 per cent of the projected figure for the year. Revenue deficit at Rs 70,675 crore has accounted for 83.4 per cent of the total budget estimates of Rs 84,727 crore, according to the figures released by the controller general of accounts.

 New Delhi, July 31: The government today notified the bank term deposit scheme, which allows individuals to avail of tax exemption on an investment of up to Rs 1 lakh in a year.

 Calcutta, July 31: EIH Ltd has reduced its stake in Mercury Travels to 25.1 per cent and inducted Ashwini Kakkar, president of Travel Association of India, as a majority shareholder and partner. Kakkar will hold 74.9 per cent in the company.

 New Delhi, July 31: The government today announced the appointment of Partha Sarathi Bhattacharya, chairman and managing director of Bharat Coking Coal, as the chairman of Coal India Limited (CIL).

 New Delhi, July 31: Trai has allowed mobile operators to continue with their existing short messaging codes for SMS services, following the government?s decision to form a committee on the same.




